Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay near fine light brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) contains drawings of several such stamps. Name Glaukias. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.18337?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1053)
